# Auto-commit and auto-push policy

**Precedence:** In this repository, this rule **overrides** global user instructions to "ask before commit" or "only commit when explicitly asked" when the current task or plan is **authorized and complete**.

## When to auto-commit

**Standing authorization:** commit and push to feature branches when the task is done and the gate passes—do not ask “may I commit?” each time (see `COMMIT_POLICY_V1.md`).

- All todos / requested work for the current task or plan are complete.
- **Pushable commit gate** has passed (see Test alignment below).
- Before committing, the agent must always:
  - Show `git status`, `git diff`, `git log -1 --oneline`.
  - Propose **one commit by default** for the task; split into multiple commits only when changes are clearly separate (e.g. docs vs code vs tests).

## What not to commit (safety exclusions)

- Never auto-commit secrets:
  - `.env`, `*.env*`, credentials, keys, tokens, or similar sensitive material.
- Never auto-commit obvious generated noise unless explicitly requested:
  - `artifacts/`, `.pytest_cache/`, `__pycache__/`, `*.sqlite*`, `*.db`, log files, or other large/generated outputs.
- Do not change git config.
- Do not use `git commit --amend` unless the user explicitly requests it.

## Auto-push behavior (branch-aware)

### Non-main branches

- After auto-commit on any branch **other than** `main` / `master`, the agent should **auto-push** to the branch’s existing upstream.
- If the current branch has no upstream yet, the first push should be `git push -u origin HEAD` (or equivalent for the default remote).
- **After push**, if there is no open PR to `main` for this branch, **open one** (`gh pr create --base main --head <branch>`). GitHub will add the `automerge` label ([`label-pr-automerge.yml`](../../.github/workflows/label-pr-automerge.yml)); when the **CI** workflow ([`ci.yml`](../../.github/workflows/ci.yml)) completes **`success`**—i.e. both **`CI / pytest`** and **`CI / docker_entrypoint`** pass—[`merge-on-green.yml`](../../.github/workflows/merge-on-green.yml) squash-merges to `main` and **Deploy VPS** can run. Do not stop at “pushed feature branch” when the intent is to ship.
- Preconditions for auto-push on non-main branches:
  - `python scripts/run_pushable_gate.py` exited 0.
  - The working tree is clean except for the intended changes.
  - No force push; fast-forward only.

### `main` / `master` branches

- Same gate as any pushable commit: `python scripts/run_pushable_gate.py`.
- If the repository uses **PR-only** delivery to `main` (see [docs/SOP/GITHUB_ZERO_TOUCH_MERGE.md](../../docs/SOP/GITHUB_ZERO_TOUCH_MERGE.md)), **do not** auto-push directly to `main`. Push a **feature branch** and open a PR so GitHub runs the full **CI** workflow (pytest + docker_entrypoint) before merge.
- No secrets / artifacts in the commit; no force push or history rewrite.

## When not to auto-push

The agent must NOT auto-push when:

- Push would require `--force`, history rewrite, or unsafe conflict resolution.
- Remote rejects the push (branch protection, required checks) — surface the error; do not retry with riskier options.
- Pushable gate failed, or was not run for non-docs-only code changes.

## Test alignment (canonical)

Authoritative detail: [docs/SOP/COMMIT_POLICY_V1.md](../../docs/SOP/COMMIT_POLICY_V1.md). Operator setup: [docs/SOP/AGENT_GIT_SETUP.md](../../docs/SOP/AGENT_GIT_SETUP.md).

### Pushable gate (run before every commit)

```bash
python scripts/run_pushable_gate.py
```

Tiered locally (docs-only / targeted pytest / full pytest). **PR CI** still runs full ruff + pytest + docker entrypoint.

### Implied-lab UI (PR / merge, not commit)

If the task touched `src/viz/**` or UI smoke scripts, remind the user (or run when asked) before PR merge:

```bash
python scripts/run_mvp1_dual_implied_lab_smoke.py
```

Do not block commit on dual smoke (environment-sensitive).

### Merge to `main`

GitHub **CI** = **`CI / pytest`** (ruff + full pytest) **and** **`CI / docker_entrypoint`** (Docker + Streamlit smoke). Local gate speeds iteration; docker smoke runs on GitHub unless replicated locally.
